- 'Top 5 performance metrics' refers to the highest metric values for each model, ranked in descending order;
- 'Top 3 feature importances' refers to the highest feature importances for each model, ranked in descending order;
- 'Performance metrics' are measures used to evaluate the effectiveness of a machine learning model;
- 'Feature importance' indicates the relative importance of input features in contributing to the model's predictions.

- "Adorned with annotations" refers to the images that have received the most annotations;
- "Over the past year" means the period from one year ago to the present;
- "Top 5" indicates the images with the highest number of annotations.

- 'geographically marked' refers to images with valid latitude and longitude coordinates;
- 'tended to by the annotators' refers to images that have annotations made by users with the role 'annotator';
- 'average length of their annotations' is calculated as the average length of the text in the `annotation_text` field;
- 'more than five annotations' means the images have at least six annotations.

- "Most recent image" refers to the image with the latest `created_at` timestamp within each organization;
- "Most recent annotation" refers to the annotation with the latest `annotation_date` for each image;
- "Location" refers to the latitude and longitude coordinates of the image.

- "latest performance metrics" refer to the most recent metric values recorded for each model;
- "feature importances" represent the relative importance of features in the model's predictions;
- "model ID" uniquely identifies each machine learning model;
- "updated_at" indicates the timestamp when the data was last updated, ensuring the latest data is selected.

- `object_id` is the unique identifier for each image;
- `latitude` and `longitude` provide the geographical location of the image;
- `image_id` is the ID of the image being annotated;
- `annotation_id` is the unique identifier for each annotation.

- "Recently blossomed" refers to images created within the last year;
- "Frequently annotated" refers to images with more annotations than the average number of annotations for images annotated within the last six months;
- "Gardeners" refer to the annotators who add annotations to the images.

sql:
SELECT COUNT(*)
FROM images
WHERE org_id IS NOT NULL;

SELECT AVG(pov_exp) AS average_pov_experience
FROM images
WHERE tags LIKE '%landscape%';

